    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> Instead create a search component, and mark that one as asynchronous instead of every single one.\n\nWhile this would be nice, and i have tried it. That still causes the same problems to occur.\n\n```html\n<div id=\"app\">\n   <my-wrapper>\n      <ais-instant-search ...>\n         <ais-search-box ...>...</ais-search-box>\n         <ais-refinement-list ...>...</ais-refinement-list>\n         <ais-hierarchical-menu ...>...</ais-hierarchical-menu>\n         <ais-range-input ...>...</ais-range-input>\n         <ais-current-refinements ...>...</ais-current-refinements>\n         <ais-hits-per-page ...>...</ais-hits-per-page>\n         <ais-sort-by ...>...</ais-sort-by>\n         <ais-pagination ...>...</ais-pagination>\n         <ais-stats ...>...</ais-stats>\n            <ais-hits>...</ais-hits>\n      </ais-instant-search>\n   </my-wrapper>\n</div>\n```\n\nIf i import and locally register the components solely in `my-wrapper` i will get the errors that `ais-instant-search`, `ais-search-box`, `ais-...` are not found.\nYou used to be able to use local components with `inline-template` but that has been deprecated https://v3-migration.vuejs.org/breaking-changes/inline-template-attribute.html#inline-template-attribute\n\nRegistering them as async components globally, and eager locally also still results in the same amount of requests being done.",
